<p id="Par29" class="p">The aim of the PCA is to find a linear combination of the driver variables that represents the one-dimensional projection with the largest possible variance. First, each driver time series 
 <italic class="italic">x</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub> is normalized by centering on its mean (subtracting 
 <inline-formula id="IEq1" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M1" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\bar x_i$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M2" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mover accent="true" class="mover">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mo class="mo">¯</mo>
      </mover>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2019_8633_Article_IEq1.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>) and scaling to unit variance (divide by one standard deviation 
 <italic class="italic">σ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub>). Thus,
 <disp-formula id="Equ1" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">1</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M3" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${\mathbf{X}} = x_i^\prime = \frac{{x_i - \bar x_i}}{{\sigma _i}}.$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M4" display="block" class="math">
    <mi mathvariant="bold" class="mi">X</mi>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">x</mi>
